Some extremely useful additional data on the version report would be:

* Mouseover points where the projected completion date line intersects the release date vertical line.  This would let us easily see just how many story points of issues need to be cut from the version in order to meet the release date.
* A mouseover point (or on-screen text) where the projected completion line crosses today indicating the average velocity against the version up to this point.  This is the gradient of the line at that point, or the total points completed as of today divided by say weeks of the version, given a per-week velocity.  Othewise, an on screen indication of total days so far so that we can calculate velocity over whatever time period we want without having to figure out how many days we are into development.

